        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cook the soup",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat {{extra-virgin-olive-oil}} of olive oil in a large pot over a medium-low heat. Add the {{onion}} onion and {{garlic}} of garlic and cook for 6 minutes until soft.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{carrot}} carrots and cook for 3 minutes. Add the {{courgette}} courgettes, {{green-beans}} of green beans, and {{tomato}} chopped tomatoes. Stir to combine.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the {{cannellini-beans}} of white beans and pour in {{stock-vegetable}} of hot stock. Season with salt. Bring to a simmer and cook for 15 minutes.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add {{pasta-dried}} of pasta and cook for the time given on the packet. The soup should be thick and well-loaded with vegetables and pasta.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Make the pistou",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "While the pasta cooks, pound {{basil}} of basil leaves and {{garlic}} of garlic together in a pestle and mortar (or use a food processor) until a rough paste forms. Pour in {{extra-virgin-olive-oil}} of olive oil in a thin stream while stirring. Add {{parmesan}} of Parmesan if using. Season with salt.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Ladle the hot soup into bowls. Add a generous spoonful of pistou to each bowl and let diners stir it in themselves.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Make the pistou as close to serving as possible, ideally no more than 20 minutes ahead. Keep a small piece of cling film pressed directly onto its surface to slow oxidation.",
                "cause": "Basil oxidises quickly once pounded and exposed to air.",
                "symptom": "Pistou has turned brown"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Simmer uncovered for an additional 10 minutes to reduce. The pistou thickens the bowl further once stirred in, so a slightly thin soup is preferable to an overly thick one.",
                "cause": "The vegetables released a lot of moisture, diluting the stock.",
                "symptom": "Soup is too watery"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Add the pasta only when ready to serve. If it has absorbed too much liquid, add hot stock or water and reheat gently.",
                "cause": "The soup was left to stand after the pasta was added.",
                "symptom": "Pasta has swollen and absorbed all the liquid"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Use one clove rather than two, or blanch the garlic in boiling water for 30 seconds to mellow it before pounding.",
                "cause": "Two cloves of raw garlic in the pistou can be strong.",
                "symptom": "Pistou tastes sharp from raw garlic"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Soupe au pistou is the centrepiece of summer cooking in Provence and the French Riviera, where it crosses into the Ligurian cooking of nearby Italy. The soup varies by season and what is in the garden: broad beans in spring, courgettes in summer, dried beans in autumn. The pistou ,  a word that gives its name to the pestle used to make it ,  is closely related to Genoese pesto but traditionally made without pine nuts. The soup is eaten throughout Provence in summer as a filling midday meal, often with good crusty bread.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
